info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 14 at 11:17AM CDT until further notice by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Spirit River near Spirit Falls affecting Lincoln County. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS MORNING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Spirit River near Spirit Falls. * WHEN...From this morning until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 9.5 feet, Water is likely covering parts of Spirit Falls Road and Bridge Road. Flooding is likely occurring along Ritche Creek and Squaw Creek. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 10:30 AM CDT Thursday the stage was 8.8 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 10:30 AM CDT Thursday was 8.9 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 8.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued late tonight.
